# Supabase SQL — summary convention

Human-readable documentation: **`docs/SUPABASE_SQL.md`**.

When the user must execute SQL in Supabase (typically **Dashboard → SQL Editor**), make that explicit at the end of the task summary.

Use **ALL CAPS** for the action line so it stands out, for example:

**RUN IN SUPABASE SQL EDITOR:** (then: which file/section, or paste the exact `CREATE POLICY` / migration snippet they need.)

Keep the caps line short; use normal sentence case for surrounding explanation. Do not put entire summaries in caps.
